    <spirit:description>The purpose of this interface is the control of device quiescence.
There are 2 signal groups:
  the activity indicator (QACTIVE), and
  the handshake signal group (QREQn, QACCEPTn, and QDENY).
A QACTIVE only interface is supported.
QACTIVE may be omitted if handshake signals are present.
To support the handshake, both QREQn and QACCEPTn must be present, and QDENY is optional.
For more information please refer to the AMBA Low Power Interface Specification ARM IHI 0068D : http://www.arm.com/support/AMBA.html</spirit:description>
